Transaction : Exchange of value between two parties

Accounts: transactions are recorded under accounts

Personal Account : Related to entity ( Debtor or creditor ) --> Acc receivable & payable , liabilities
Real Account: we can touch and see (Cash,car,bank,mobile) ---> Asset accounts
Nominal Account: we cannot see , but can be felt ( Salaries, proft, loss, cost, Expense)

Accounting:

Method of storing transactions and driving business insights from the stored transactional data using analytical processing.

Accounting Principles : GAAP, STAT , IFRS

GAAP: Generally accepted accounting principles 

* Each country has it's own accounting principles, US GAAP. India GAAP.

IFRS : international financial reporting standards 

* global version --> for different economic view point 

GAAP principles:

Business entity : business is seperate from its Owner
Money Measurement : Record only what can be expressed as money
Going concern : Assume business will continue
Accounting period : Financial / Fiscial Year divided into period ...

Statutory : Accounting for compliance , not for growth ( Required by law )
